HEADWORD: Contraindicant
<hw>Con"tra*in"di*cant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Something, as a symptom, indicating that the
usual mode of treatment is not to be followed.</def>
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

